    "Those serving significant user bases may also have to conduct risk assessments under Article 26 and can voluntarily opt into transparency around recommender systems as per Article 29.Critics argue that these compliance burdens may be disproportionate for smaller entities with limited resources [109].",
    "Creating accessible reporting systems, content review teams, and internal redress mechanisms requires significant staffing and investment.",
    "Conducting recurring risk assessments also necessitates sizable internal capacity.There are concerns these obligations may disproportionately impact startups and new innovators aiming to compete with tech incumbents, thereby contributing to anti-competitive effects that favor established giants with sizable compliance budgets.",
    "Loss of smaller European platforms is also feared given difficulties in competing with major US players.",
    "As such, specific impacts on smaller intermediaries need careful evaluation during initial DSA roll-out."
